{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Soak urad and kidney beans for at least 8 hours or overnight in plenty of water. Rinse well twice, ensuring any grit is removed, then drain.","Place soaked and drained urad and kidney beans, water, 10 g ginger and chilli powder in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>30 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr> until beans are soft. Drain, reserving cooking water and set aside.","Place ghee and cumin seeds in mixing bowl then fry <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add onions and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add remaining 10 g ginger, garlic, salt and tomatoes then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula then cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 0.5<\/nobr>.","Add reserved cooked dal then cook <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add 150 g reserved cooking water then simmer <nobr>15 min\/90°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add cream and garam masala then cook <nobr>5 min\/90°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Serve garnished with a drizzle of cream."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["140 g urad beans (black lentils)","40 g kidney beans, dried","600 g water, plus extra for soaking","20 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 tsp Kashmiri chilli powder","20 g ghee","2 tsp cumin seeds","70 g onions, quartered","6 garlic cloves","1 tsp fine sea salt","100 g tinned chopped tomatoes","50 - 70 g double cream, to taste, plus extra for serving","1 tsp garam masala"]}],"id":"r112707","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZwnMNPUwXf0\/XZVRvIxs33I\/AAAAAAAAdSY\/1gQyCJ5Zn5M3k12wlmZUMPqSDecRoGFEgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_vjBp0P9gOlhfIKUE.png","title":"Dal Makhani","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.7 g","fat":"8.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20.7 g","calories":"812 kJ \/ 194 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jug, fine sieve","hintsAndTricks":["For a thicker dal, only add 100 g reserved cooking water in step 7.","This black lentil and kidney bean based Punjabi dish is served right across India. It is a rich vegetarian dish that can be served with bread or rice, or alongside other curries as part of a selection. Because of the lengthy total time (due to the soaking of the lentils and beans) this dish needs a bit of planning. It traditionally appears at weddings and parties."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","9h 30m","6 portions"]}